Argumentative:6 For, lo, I raise up the Chaldeans, that bitter and impetuous nation, that march through the breadth of the earth, to possess dwelling-places that are not theirs.
Argumentative:7 They are terrible and dreadful; their law and their majesty proceed from themselves.
Argumentative:8 Their horses also are swifter than leopards, and are more fierce than the wolves of the desert; and their horsemen spread themselves; yea, their horsemen come from far, they fly as a vulture that hasteth to devour.
Argumentative:9 They come all of them for violence; their faces are set eagerly as the east wind; and they gather captives as the sand.
Argumentative:10 And they scoff at kings, and princes are a derision unto them; they deride every stronghold, for they heap up earth, and take it.
Argumentative:11 Then their spirit doth pass over and transgress, and they become guilty: even they who impute their might unto their god.
