Argumentative:Ahavat Israel - Tanach: Hoshea - Hosea Ahavat Israel Am Israel Torat Israel Eretz Israel Jewish Texts Tanach Pirkei Avot Path Just ClassAds Postcard Forum Music Humor Games Books Videos About Feedback Recommend Wallpaper Privacy Copyright Tanach: Hoshea - Hosea Treisar - The Minor Prophets Text: Hosea1 | Hosea2 | Hosea3 | Hosea4 | Hosea5 | Hosea6 | Hosea7 | Hosea8 | Hosea9 | Hosea10 | Hosea11 | Hosea12 | Hosea13 | Hosea14 Hosea1 1 THE WORD of HaShem that came unto Hosea the son of Beeri, in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel.
Argumentative:4 And HaShem said unto him: 'Call his name Jezreel; for yet a little while, and I will visit the blood of Jezreel upon the house of Jehu, and will cause to cease the kingdom of the house of Israel.
Argumentative:' 4 For the children of Israel shall sit solitary many days without king, and without prince, and without sacrifice, and without pillar, and without ephod or teraphim; 5 afterward shall the children of Israel return, and seek HaShem their G-d, and David their king; and shall come trembling unto HaShem and to His goodness in the end of days. Hosea4 1 Hear the word of HaShem, ye children of Israel!
Argumentative:for HaShem hath a controversy with the inhabitants of the land, because there is no truth, nor mercy, nor knowledge of G-d in the land.
Argumentative:2 Swearing and lying, and killing, and stealing, and committing adultery!
Argumentative:they break all bounds, and blood toucheth blood.
Argumentative:3 Therefore doth the land mourn, and every one that dwelleth therein doth languish, with the beasts of the field, and the fowls of heaven; yea, the fishes of the sea also are taken away.
Argumentative:4 Yet let no man strive, neither let any man reprove; for thy people are as they that strive with the priest.
Argumentative:5 Therefore shalt thou stumble in the day, and the prophet also shall stumble with thee in the night; and I will destroy thy mother.
Argumentative:6 My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge; because thou hast rejected knowledge, I will also reject thee, that thou shalt be no priest to Me; seeing thou hast forgotten the law of thy G-d, I also will forget thy children.
Argumentative:7 The more they were increased, the more they sinned against Me; I will change their glory into shame.
Argumentative:8 They feed on the sin of My people, and set their heart on their iniquity.
Argumentative:9 And it is like people, like priest; and I will punish him for his ways, and will recompense him his doings.
Argumentative:10 And they shall eat, and not have enough, they shall commit harlotry, and shall not increase; because they have left off to take heed to HaShem.
Argumentative:12 My people ask counsel at their stock, and their staff declareth unto them; for the spirit of harlotry hath caused them to err, and they have gone astray from under their G-d. 13 They sacrifice upon the tops of the mountains, and offer upon the hills, under oaks and poplars and terebinths, because the shadow thereof is good; therefore your daughters commit harlotry, and your daughters-in-law commit adultery.
Argumentative:14 I will not punish your daughters when they commit harlotry, nor your daughters-in-law when they commit adultery; for they themselves consort with lewd women, and they sacrifice with harlots; and the people that is without understanding is distraught.
Argumentative:' 16 For Israel is stubborn like a stubborn heifer; now shall HaShem feed them as a lamb in a large place?
Argumentative:17 Ephraim is joined to idols; let him alone.
Argumentative:18 When their carouse is over, they take to harlotry; her rulers deeply love dishonour.
Argumentative:19 The wind hath bound her up in her skirts; and they shall be ashamed because of their sacrifices.
Argumentative:2 And they that fall away are gone deep in making slaughter; and I am rejected of them all.
Argumentative:3 I, even I, know Ephraim, and Israel is not hid from Me; for now, O Ephraim, thou hast committed harlotry, Israel is defiled.
Argumentative:4 Their doings will not suffer them to return unto their G-d; for the spirit of harlotry is within them, and they know not HaShem.
Argumentative:5 But the pride of Israel shall testify to his face; and Israel and Ephraim shall stumble in their iniquity, Judah also shall stumble with them.
Argumentative:6 With their flocks and with their herds they shall go to seek HaShem, but they shall not find Him; He hath withdrawn Himself from them.
Argumentative:10 The princes of Judah are like them that remove the landmark; I will pour out My wrath upon them like water.
Argumentative:11 Oppressed is Ephraim, crushed in his right; because he willingly walked after filth.
Argumentative:13 And when Ephraim saw his sickness, and Judah his wound, Ephraim went to Assyria, and sent to King Contentious; but he is not able to heal you, neither shall he cure you of your wound.
Argumentative:15 I will go and return to My place, till they acknowledge their guilt, and seek My face; in their trouble they will seek Me earnestly: Hosea6 1 'Come, and let us return unto HaShem; for He hath torn, and He will heal us, He hath smitten, and He will bind us up.
Argumentative:3 And let us know, eagerly strive to know HaShem, His going forth is sure as the morning; and He shall come unto us as the rain, as the latter rain that watereth the earth.
Argumentative:for your goodness is as a morning cloud, and as the dew that early passeth away.
Argumentative:7 But they like men have transgressed the covenant; there have they dealt treacherously against Me.
Argumentative:8 Gilead is a city of them that work iniquity, it is covered with footprints of blood.
Argumentative:9 And as troops of robbers wait for a man, so doth the company of priests; they murder in the way toward Shechem; yea, they commit enormity.
Argumentative:10 In the house of Israel I have seen a horrible thing; there harlotry is found in Ephraim, Israel is defiled.
Argumentative:When I would turn the captivity of My people, Hosea7 1 when I would heal Israel, then is the iniquity of Ephraim uncovered, and the wickedness of Samaria, for they commit falsehood; and the thief entereth in, and the troop of robbers maketh a raid without.
Argumentative:2 And let them not say to their heart--I remember all their wickedness; now their own doings have beset them about, they are before My face.
Argumentative:3 They make the king glad with their wickedness, and the princes with their lies.
Argumentative:4 They are all adulterers, as an oven heated by the baker, who ceaseth to stir from the kneading of the dough until it be leavened.
Argumentative:5 On the day of our king the princes make him sick with the heat of wine, he stretcheth out his hand with scorners.
Argumentative:6 For they have made ready their heart like an oven, while they lie in wait; their baker sleepeth all the night, in the morning it burneth as a flaming fire.
Argumentative:7 They are all hot as an oven, and devour their judges; all their kings are fallen, there is none among them that calleth unto Me.
Argumentative:8 Ephraim, he mixeth himself with the peoples; Ephraim is become a cake not turned.
Argumentative:9 Strangers have devoured his strength, and he knoweth it not; yea, gray hairs are here and there upon him, and he knoweth it not.
Argumentative:for they have strayed from Me; Destruction unto them!
Argumentative:for they have transgressed against Me; Shall I then redeem them, seeing they have spoken lies against Me?
Argumentative:14 And they have not cried unto Me with their heart, though they wail upon their beds; they assemble themselves for corn and wine, they rebel against Me.
Argumentative:16 They return, but not upwards; they are become like a deceitful bow; their princes shall fall by the sword for the rage of their tongue; this shall be their derision in the land of Egypt.
Argumentative:Hosea8 1 Set the horn to thy mouth.
Argumentative:As a vulture he cometh against the house of HaShem; because they have transgressed My covenant, and trespassed against My law.
Argumentative:3 Israel hath cast off that which is good; the enemy shall pursue him.
Argumentative:4 They have set up kings, but not from Me, they have made princes, and I knew it not; of their silver and their gold have they made them idols, that they may be cut off.
Argumentative:5 Thy calf, O Samaria, is cast off; Mine anger is kindled against them; how long will it be ere they attain to innocency?
Argumentative:7 For they sow the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind; it hath no stalk, the bud that shall yield no meal; if so be it yield, strangers shall swallow it up.
Argumentative:8 Israel is swallowed up; now are they become among the nations as a vessel wherein is no value.
Argumentative:9 For they are gone up to Assyria, like a wild ass alone by himself; Ephraim hath hired lovers.
Argumentative:12 Though I write for him never so many things of My Law, they are accounted as a stranger's.
Argumentative:13 As for the sacrifices that are made by fire unto Me, let them sacrifice flesh and eat it, for HaShem accepteth them not.
Argumentative:Now will He remember their iniquity, and punish their sins; they shall return to Egypt.
Argumentative:Hosea9 1 Rejoice not, O Israel, unto exultation, like the peoples, for thou hast gone astray from thy G-d, thou hast loved a harlot's hire upon every corn-floor.
Argumentative:2 The threshing-floor and the wine-press shall not feed them, and the new wine shall fail her.
Argumentative:3 They shall not dwell in HaShem'S land; but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean food in Assyria.
Argumentative:4 They shall not pour out wine-offerings to HaShem, neither shall they be pleasing unto Him; their sacrifices shall be unto them as the bread of mourners, all that eat thereof shall be polluted; for their bread shall be for their appetite, it shall not come into the house of HaShem.
Argumentative:6 For, lo, they are gone away from destruction, yet Egypt shall gather them up, Memphis shall bury them; their precious treasures of silver, nettles shall possess them, thorns shall be in their tents.
Argumentative:7 The days of visitation are come, the days of recompense are come, Israel shall know it.
Argumentative:The prophet is a fool, the man of the spirit is mad!
Argumentative:8 Ephraim is a watchman with my G-d; as for the prophet, a fowler's snare is in all his ways, and enmity in the house of his G-d. 9 They have deeply corrupted themselves, as in the days of Gibeah; He will remember their iniquity, He will punish their sins.
Argumentative:11 As for Ephraim, their glory shall fly away like a bird; there shall be no birth, and none with child, and no conception.
Argumentative:14 Give them, O LORD, whatsoever Thou wilt give; give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.
Argumentative:15 All their wickedness is in Gilgal, for there I hated them; because of the wickedness of their doings I will drive them out of My house; I will love them no more, all their princes are rebellious.
Argumentative:16 Ephraim is smitten, their root is dried up, they shall bear no fruit; yea, though they bring forth, yet will I slay the beloved fruit of their womb.
Argumentative:17 My G-d will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto Him; and they shall be wanderers among the nations.
Argumentative:Hosea10 1 Israel was a luxuriant vine, which put forth fruit freely: as his fruit increased, he increased his altars; the more goodly his land was, the more goodly were his pillars.
Argumentative:2 Their heart is divided; now shall they bear their guilt; He will break down their altars, He will spoil their pillars.
Argumentative:' 4 They speak words, they swear falsely, they make covenants; thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.
Argumentative:5 The inhabitants of Samaria shall be in dread for the calves of Beth-aven; for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof shall tremble for it, for its glory, because it is departed from it.
Argumentative:6 It also shall be carried unto Assyria, for a present to King Contentious; Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.
Argumentative:' 9 From the days of Gibeah thou hast sinned, O Israel; there they stood; no battle was to overtake them in Gibeah, nor the children of arrogancy.
Argumentative:10 When it is My desire, I will chastise them; and the peoples shall be gathered against them, when they are yoked to their two rings.
Argumentative:11 And Ephraim is a heifer well broken, that loveth to thresh, and I have passed over upon her fair neck; I will make Ephraim to ride, Judah shall plow, Jacob shall break his clods.
Argumentative:12 Sow to yourselves according to righteousness, reap according to mercy, break up your fallow ground; for it is time to seek HaShem, till He come and cause righteousness to rain upon you.
Argumentative:13 Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity, ye have eaten the fruit of lies; for thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude of thy mighty men.
Argumentative:14 Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy hosts, and all thy fortresses shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Beth-arbel in the day of battle; the mother was dashed in pieces with her children.
Argumentative:15 So hath Beth-el done unto you because of your great wickedness; at daybreak is the king of Israel utterly cut off.
Argumentative:2 The more they called them, the more they went from them; they sacrificed unto the Baalim, and offered to graven images.
Argumentative:5 He shall not return into the land of Egypt, but the Assyrian shall be his king, because they refused to return.
Argumentative:6 And the sword shall fall upon his cities, and shall consume his bars, and devour them, because of their own counsels.
Argumentative:7 And My people are in suspense about returning to Me; and though they call them upwards, none at all will lift himself up.
Argumentative:10 They shall walk after HaShem, who shall roar like a lion; for He shall roar, and the children shall come trembling from the west.
Argumentative:He loveth to oppress.
Argumentative:Hosea13 1 When Ephraim spoke, there was trembling, he exalted himself in Israel; but when he became guilty through Baal, he died.
Argumentative:2 And now they sin more and more, and have made them molten images of their silver, according to their own understanding, even idols, all of them the work of the craftsmen; of them they say: 'They that sacrifice men kiss calves.
Argumentative:' 3 Therefore they shall be as the morning cloud, and as the dew that early passeth away, as the chaff that is driven with the wind out of the threshing-floor, and as the smoke out of the window.
Argumentative:5 I did know thee in the wilderness, in the land of great drought.
Argumentative:6 When they were fed, they became full, they were filled, and their heart was exalted; therefore have they forgotten Me.
Argumentative:9 It is thy destruction, O Israel, that thou art against Me, against thy help.
Argumentative:and thy judges, of whom thou saidst: 'Give me a king and princes!
Argumentative:13 The throes of a travailing woman shall come upon him; he is an unwise son; for it is time he should not tarry in the place of the breaking forth of children.
Argumentative:14 Shall I ransom them from the power of the nether-world?
Argumentative:Ho, thy plagues, O death!
Argumentative:Ho, thy destruction, O netherworld!
Argumentative:15 For though he be fruitful among the reed-plants, an east wind shall come, the wind of HaShem coming up from the wilderness, and his spring shall become dry, and his fountain shall be dried up; he shall spoil the treasure of all precious vessels.
Argumentative:For the ways of HaShem are right, and the just do walk in them; but transgressors do stumble therein.
Argumentative:top of page Find us on Facebook Follow us on Twitter See us on YouTube Recommend This Page To A Friend Take the Israeli Opinion Poll!
