Argumentative:21 The lips of the righteous feed many; but the foolish die for want of understanding.
Argumentative:Ahavat Israel - Tanach: Mishlei - Proverbs Ahavat Israel Am Israel Torat Israel Eretz Israel Jewish Texts Tanach Pirkei Avot Path Just ClassAds Postcard Forum Music Humor Games Books Videos About Feedback Recommend Wallpaper Privacy Copyright Tanach: Mishlei - Proverbs Ketuvim - The Writings Text: Proverbs1 | Proverbs2 | Proverbs3 | Proverbs4 | Proverbs5 | Proverbs6 | Proverbs7 | Proverbs8 | Proverbs9 | Proverbs10 | Proverbs11 | Proverbs12 | Proverbs13 | Proverbs14 | Proverbs15 | Proverbs16 | Proverbs17 | Proverbs18 | Proverbs19 | Proverbs20 | Proverbs21 | Proverbs22 | Proverbs23 | Proverbs24 | Proverbs25 | Proverbs26 | Proverbs27 | Proverbs28 | Proverbs29 | Proverbs30 | Proverbs31 Proverbs1 1 THE PROVERBS of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel; 2 To know wisdom and instruction; to comprehend the words of understanding; 3 To receive the discipline of wisdom, justice, and right, and equity; 4 To give prudence to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion; 5 That the wise man may hear, and increase in learning, and the man of understanding may attain unto wise counsels; 6 To understand a proverb, and a figure; the words of the wise, and their dark sayings.
Argumentative:11 If they say: 'Come with us, let us lie in wait for blood, let us lurk for the innocent without cause; 12 Let us swallow them up alive as the grave, and whole, as those that go down into the pit; 13 We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil; 14 Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse'-- 15 My son, walk not thou in the way with them, restrain thy foot from their path; 16 For their feet run to evil, and they make haste to shed blood.
Argumentative:17 For in vain the net is spread in the eyes of any bird; 18 And these lie in wait for their own blood, they lurk for their own lives.
Argumentative:19 So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; it taketh away the life of the owners thereof.
Argumentative:And how long will scorners delight them in scorning, and fools hate knowledge?
Argumentative:29 For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of HaShem; 30 They would none of my counsel, they despised all my reproof.
Argumentative:31 Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.
Argumentative:32 For the waywardness of the thoughtless shall slay them, and the confidence of fools shall destroy them.
Argumentative:' Proverbs2 1 My son, if thou wilt receive my words, and lay up my commandments with thee; 2 So that thou make thine ear attend unto wisdom, and thy heart incline to discernment; 3 Yea, if thou call for understanding, and lift up thy voice for discernment; 4 If thou seek her as silver, and search for her as for hid treasures; 5 Then shalt thou understand the fear of HaShem, and find the knowledge of G-d. 6 For HaShem giveth wisdom, out of His mouth cometh knowledge and discernment; 7 He layeth up sound wisdom for the upright, He is a shield to them that walk in integrity; 8 That He may guard the paths of justice, and preserve the way of His godly ones.
Argumentative:9 Then shalt thou understand righteousness and justice, and equity, yea, every good path.
Argumentative:21 For the upright shall dwell in the land, and the whole-hearted shall remain in it.
Argumentative:22 But the wicked shall be cut off from the land, and the faithless shall be plucked up out of it.
Argumentative:3 Let not kindness and truth forsake thee; bind them about thy neck, write them upon the table of thy heart; 4 So shalt thou find grace and good favour in the sight of G-d and man.
Argumentative:5 Trust in HaShem with all thy heart, and lean not upon thine own understanding.
Argumentative:6 In all thy ways acknowledge Him, and He will direct thy paths.
Argumentative:7 Be not wise in thine own eyes; fear HaShem, and depart from evil; 8 It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones.
Argumentative:9 Honour HaShem with thy substance, and with the first-fruits of all thine increase; 10 So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy vats shall overflow with new wine.
Argumentative:11 My son, despise not the chastening of HaShem, neither spurn thou His correction; 12 For whom HaShem loveth He correcteth, even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.
Argumentative:13 Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that obtaineth understanding.
Argumentative:14 For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.
Argumentative:15 She is more precious than rubies; and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.
Argumentative:18 She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her, and happy is every one that holdest her fast.
Argumentative:21 My son, let not them depart from thine eyes; keep sound wisdom and discretion; 22 So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.
Argumentative:23 Then shalt thou walk in thy way securely, and thou shalt not dash thy foot.
Argumentative:25 Be not afraid of sudden terror, neither of the destruction of the wicked, when it cometh; 26 For HaShem will be thy confidence, and will keep thy foot from being caught.
Argumentative:27 Withhold not good from him to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thy hand to do it.
Argumentative:29 Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.
Argumentative:30 Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.
Argumentative:31 Envy thou not the man of violence, and choose none of his ways.
Argumentative:32 For the perverse is an abomination to HaShem; but His counsel is with the upright.
Argumentative:33 The curse of HaShem is in the house of the wicked; but He blesseth the habitation of the righteous.
Argumentative:34 If it concerneth the scorners, He scorneth them, but unto the humble He giveth grace.
Argumentative:35 The wise shall inherit honour; but as for the fools, they carry away shame.
Argumentative:Proverbs4 1 Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know understanding.
Argumentative:12 When thou goest, thy step shall not be straitened; and if thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.
Argumentative:14 Enter not into the path of the wicked, and walk not in the way of evil men.
Argumentative:16 For they sleep not, except they have done evil; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause some to fall.
Argumentative:18 But the path of the righteous is as the light of dawn, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.
Argumentative:19 The way of the wicked is as darkness; they know not at what they stumble.
Argumentative:21 Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them in the midst of thy heart.
Argumentative:22 For they are life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh.
Argumentative:23 Above all that thou guardest keep thy heart; for out of it are the issues of life.
Argumentative:26 Make plain the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established.
Argumentative:' 15 Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.
Argumentative:18 Let thy fountain be blessed; and have joy of the wife of thy youth.
Argumentative:20 Why then wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of an alien?
Argumentative:21 For the ways of man are before the eyes of HaShem, and He maketh even all his paths.
Argumentative:22 His own iniquities shall ensnare the wicked, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sin.
Argumentative:23 He shall die for lack of instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall reel.
Argumentative:Proverbs6 1 My son, if thou art become surety for thy neighbour, if thou hast struck thy hands for a stranger-- 2 Thou art snared by the words of thy mouth, thou art caught by the words of thy mouth-- 3 Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, seeing thou art come into the hand of thy neighbour; go, humble thyself, and urge thy neighbour.
Argumentative:4 Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.
Argumentative:5 Deliver thyself as a gazelle from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.
Argumentative:When wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?
Argumentative:10 'Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep'-- 11 So shall thy poverty come as a runner, and thy want as an armed man.
Argumentative:12 A base person, a man of iniquity, is he that walketh with a froward mouth; 13 That winketh with his eyes, that scrapeth with his feet, that pointeth with his fingers; 14 Frowardness is in his heart, he deviseth evil continually; he soweth discord.
Argumentative:16 There are six things which HaShem hateth, yea, seven which are an abomination unto Him: 17 Haughty eyes, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood; 18 A heart that deviseth wicked thoughts, feet that are swift in running to evil; 19 A false witness that breatheth out lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.
Argumentative:20 My son, keep the commandment of thy father, and forsake not the teaching of thy mother; 21 Bind them continually upon thy heart, tie them about thy neck.
Argumentative:22 When thou walkest, it shall lead thee, when thou liest down, it shall watch over thee; and when thou awakest, it shall talk with thee.
Argumentative:23 For the commandment is a lamp, and the teaching is light, and reproofs of instruction are the way of life; 24 To keep thee from the evil woman, from the smoothness of the alien tongue.
Argumentative:26 For on account of a harlot a man is brought to a loaf of bread, but the adulteress hunteth for the precious life.
Argumentative:27 Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?
Argumentative:28 Or can one walk upon hot coals, and his feet not be scorched?
Argumentative:29 So he that goeth in to his neighbour's wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not go unpunished.
Argumentative:30 Men do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry; 31 But if he be found, he must restore sevenfold, he must give all the substance of his house.
Argumentative:32 He that committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding; he doeth it that would destroy his own soul.
Argumentative:33 Wounds and dishonour shall he get, and his reproach shall not be wiped away.
Argumentative:34 For jealousy is the rage of a man, and he will not spare in the day of vengeance.
Argumentative:2 Keep my commandments and live, and my teaching as the apple of thine eye.
Argumentative:3 Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thy heart.
Argumentative:18 Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning; let us solace ourselves with loves.
Argumentative:19 For my husband is not at home, he is gone a long journey; 20 He hath taken the bag of money with him; he will come home at the full moon.
Argumentative:22 He goeth after her straightway, as an ox that goeth to the slaughter, or as one in fetters to the correction of the fool; 23 Till an arrow strike through his liver; as a bird hasteneth to the snare-- and knoweth not that it is at the cost of his life.
Argumentative:27 Her house is the way to the nether-world, going down to the chambers of death.
Argumentative:5 O ye thoughtless, understand prudence, and, ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.
Argumentative:6 Hear, for I will speak excellent things, and the opening of my lips shall be right things.
Argumentative:8 All the words of my mouth are in righteousness, there is nothing perverse or crooked in them.
Argumentative:9 They are all plain to him that understandeth, and right to them that find knowledge.
Argumentative:10 Receive my instruction, and not silver, and knowledge rather than choice gold.
Argumentative:11 For wisdom is better than rubies, and all things desirable are not to be compared unto her.
Argumentative:12 I wisdom dwell with prudence, and find out knowledge of devices.
Argumentative:15 By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.
Argumentative:16 By me princes rule, and nobles, even all the judges of the earth.
Argumentative:18 Riches and honour are with me; yea, enduring riches and righteousness.
Argumentative:19 My fruit is better than gold, yea, than fine gold; and my produce than choice silver.
Argumentative:20 I walk in the way of righteousness, in the midst of the paths of justice; 21 That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance, and that I may fill their treasuries.
Argumentative:22 HaShem made me as the beginning of His way, the first of His works of old.
Argumentative:24 When there were no depths, I was brought forth; when there were no fountains abounding with water.
Argumentative:27 When He established the heavens, I was there; when He set a circle upon the face of the deep, 28 When He made firm the skies above, when the fountains of the deep showed their might, 29 When He gave to the sea His decree, that the waters should not transgress His commandment, when He appointed the foundations of the earth; 30 Then I was by Him, as a nursling; and I was daily all delight, playing always before Him, 31 Playing in His habitable earth, and my delights are with the sons of men.
Argumentative:32 Now therefore, ye children, hearken unto me; for happy are they that keep my ways.
Argumentative:34 Happy is the man that hearkeneth to me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.
Argumentative:35 For whoso findeth me findeth life, and obtaineth favour of HaShem.
Argumentative:36 But he that misseth me wrongeth his own soul; all they that hate me love death.
Argumentative:6 Forsake all thoughtlessness, and live; and walk in the way of understanding.
Argumentative:7 He that correcteth a scorner getteth to himself shame, and he that reproveth a wicked man, it becometh unto him a blot.
Argumentative:8 Reprove not a scorner, lest he hate thee; reprove a wise man, and he will love thee.
Argumentative:9 Give to a wise man, and he will be yet wiser; teach a righteous man, and he will increase in learning.
Argumentative:' 13 The woman Folly is riotous; she is thoughtless, and knoweth nothing.
Argumentative:' 18 But he knoweth not that the shades are there; that her guests are in the depths of the nether-world.
Argumentative:Proverbs10 1 The proverbs of Solomon.
Argumentative:A wise son maketh a glad father; but a foolish son is the grief of his mother.
Argumentative:2 Treasures of wickedness profit nothing; but righteousness delivereth from death.
Argumentative:3 HaShem will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish; but He thrusteth away the desire of the wicked.
Argumentative:4 He becometh poor that dealeth with a slack hand; but the hand of the diligent maketh rich.
Argumentative:5 A wise son gathereth in summer; but a son that doeth shamefully sleepeth in harvest.
Argumentative:6 Blessings are upon the head of the righteous; but the mouth of the wicked concealeth violence.
Argumentative:8 The wise in heart will receive commandments; but a prating fool shall fall.
Argumentative:9 He that walketh uprightly walketh securely; but he that perverteth his ways shall be found out.
Argumentative:10 He that winketh with the eye causeth sorrow; and a prating fool shall fall.
Argumentative:11 The mouth of the righteous is a fountain of life; but the mouth of the wicked concealeth violence.
Argumentative:12 Hatred stirreth up strifes; but love covereth all transgressions.
Argumentative:13 In the lips of him that hath discernment wisdom is found; but a rod is for the back of him that is void of understanding.
Argumentative:15 The rich man's wealth is his strong city; the ruin of the poor is their poverty.
Argumentative:16 The wages of the righteous is life; the increase of the wicked is sin.
Argumentative:17 He is in the way of life that heedeth instruction; but he that forsaketh reproof erreth.
Argumentative:18 He that hideth hatred is of lying lips; and he that uttereth a slander is a fool.
Argumentative:19 In the multitude of words there wanteth not transgression; but he that refraineth his lips is wise.
Argumentative:20 The tongue of the righteous is as choice silver; the heart of the wicked is little worth.
Argumentative:22 The blessing of HaShem, it maketh rich, and toil addeth nothing thereto.
Argumentative:23 It is as sport to a fool to do wickedness, and so is wisdom to a man of discernment.
Argumentative:24 The fear of the wicked, it shall come upon him; and the desire of the righteous shall be granted.
Argumentative:25 When the whirlwind passeth, the wicked is no more; but the righteous is an everlasting foundation.
Argumentative:26 As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, so is the sluggard to them that send him.
Argumentative:28 The hope of the righteous is gladness; but the expectation of the wicked shall perish.
Argumentative:30 The righteous shall never be moved; but the wicked shall not inhabit the land.
Argumentative:31 The mouth of the righteous buddeth with wisdom; but the froward tongue shall be cut off.
Argumentative:32 The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable; but the mouth of the wicked is all frowardness.
Argumentative:Proverbs11 1 A false balance is an abomination to HaShem; but a perfect weight is His delight.
Argumentative:2 When pride cometh, then cometh shame; but with the lowly is wisdom.
Argumentative:3 The integrity of the upright shall guide them; but the perverseness of the faithless shall destroy them.
Argumentative:4 Riches profit not in the day of wrath; but righteousness delivereth from death.
Argumentative:5 The righteousness of the sincere shall make straight his way; but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.
Argumentative:6 The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them; but the faithless shall be trapped in their own crafty device.
Argumentative:7 When a wicked man dieth, his expectation shall perish, and the hope of strength perisheth.
Argumentative:8 The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked cometh in his stead.
Argumentative:9 With his mouth the impious man destroyeth his neighbour; but through knowledge shall the righteous be delivered.
Argumentative:10 When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth; and when the wicked perish, there is joy.
Argumentative:11 By the blessing of the upright a city is exalted; but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.
Argumentative:13 He that goeth about as a talebearer revealeth secrets; but he that is of a faithful spirit concealeth a matter.
Argumentative:14 Where no wise direction is, a people falleth; but in the multitude of counsellors there is safety.
Argumentative:15 He that is surety for a stranger shall smart for it; but he that hateth them that strike hands is secure.
Argumentative:16 A gracious woman obtaineth honour; and strong men obtain riches.
Argumentative:17 The merciful man doeth good to his own soul; but he that is cruel troubleth his own flesh.
Argumentative:18 The wicked earneth deceitful wages; but he that soweth righteousness hath a sure reward.
Argumentative:19 Stedfast righteousness tendeth to life; but he that pursueth evil pursueth it to his own death.
Argumentative:20 They that are perverse in heart are an abomination to HaShem; but such as are upright in their way are His delight.
Argumentative:the evil man shall not be unpunished; but the seed of the righteous shall escape.
Argumentative:22 As a ring of gold in a swine's snout, so is a fair woman that turneth aside from discretion.
Argumentative:23 The desire of the righteous is only good; but the expectation of the wicked is wrath.
Argumentative:27 He that diligently seeketh good seeketh favour; but he that searcheth for evil, it shall come unto him.
Argumentative:28 He that trusteth in his riches shall fall; but the righteous shall flourish as foliage.
Argumentative:29 He that troubleth his own house shall inherit the wind; and the foolish shall be servant to the wise of heart.
Argumentative:30 The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life; and he that is wise winneth souls.
Argumentative:31 Behold, the righteous shall be requited in the earth; how much more the wicked and the sinner!
Argumentative:Proverbs12 1 Whoso loveth knowledge loveth correction; but he that is brutish hateth reproof.
Argumentative:2 A good man shall obtain favour of HaShem; but a man of wicked devices will He condemn.
Argumentative:3 A man shall not be established by wickedness; but the root of the righteous shall never be moved.
Argumentative:5 The thoughts of the righteous are right; but the counsels of the wicked are deceit.
Argumentative:7 The wicked are overthrown, and are not; but the house of the righteous shall stand.
Argumentative:8 A man shall be commended according to his intelligence; but he that is of a distorted understanding shall be despised.
Argumentative:9 Better is he that is lightly esteemed, and hath a servant, than he that playeth the man of rank, and lacketh bread.
Argumentative:10 A righteous man regardeth the life of his beast; but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.
Argumentative:11 He that tilleth his ground shall have plenty of bread; but he that followeth after vain things is void of understanding.
Argumentative:12 The wicked desireth the prey of evil men; but the root of the righteous yieldeth fruit.
Argumentative:13 In the transgression of the lips is a snare to the evil man; but the righteous cometh out of trouble.
Argumentative:14 A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth, and the doings of a man's hands shall be rendered unto him.
Argumentative:15 The way of a fool is straight in his own eyes; but he that is wise hearkeneth unto counsel.
Argumentative:16 A fool's vexation is presently known; but a prudent man concealeth shame.
Argumentative:17 He that breatheth forth truth uttereth righteousness; but a false witness deceit.
Argumentative:18 There is that speaketh like the piercings of a sword; but the tongue of the wise is health.
Argumentative:20 Deceit is in the heart of them that devise evil; but to the counsellors of peace is joy.
Argumentative:21 There shall no mischief befall the righteous; but the wicked are filled with evil.
Argumentative:23 A prudent man concealeth knowledge; but the heart of fools proclaimeth foolishness.
Argumentative:25 Care in the heart of a man boweth it down; but a good word maketh it glad.
Argumentative:26 The righteous is guided by his friend; but the way of the wicked leadeth them astray.
Argumentative:27 The slothful man shall not hunt his prey; but the precious substance of men is to be diligent.
Argumentative:28 In the way of righteousness is life, and in the pathway thereof there is no death.
Argumentative:Proverbs13 1 A wise son is instructed of his father; but a scorner heareth not rebuke.
Argumentative:2 A man shall eat good from the fruit of his mouth; but the desire of the faithless is violence.
Argumentative:4 The soul of the sluggard desireth, and hath nothing; but the soul of the diligent shall be abundantly gratified.
Argumentative:5 A righteous man hateth lying; but a wicked man behaveth vilely and shamefully.
Argumentative:6 Righteousness guardeth him that is upright in the way; but wickedness overthroweth the sinner.
Argumentative:7 There is that pretendeth himself rich, yet hath nothing; there is that pretendeth himself poor, yet hath great wealth.
Argumentative:8 The ransom of a man's life are his riches; but the poor heareth no threatening.
Argumentative:9 The light of the righteous rejoiceth; but the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.
Argumentative:10 By pride cometh only contention; but with the well-advised is wisdom.
Argumentative:11 Wealth gotten by vanity shall be diminished; but he that gathereth little by little shall increase.
Argumentative:12 Hope deferred maketh the heart sick; but desire fulfilled is a tree of life.
Argumentative:13 Whoso despiseth the word shall suffer thereby; but he that feareth the commandment shall be rewarded.
Argumentative:14 The teaching of the wise is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.
Argumentative:15 Good understanding giveth grace; but the way of the faithless is harsh.
Argumentative:16 Every prudent man dealeth with forethought; but a fool unfoldeth folly.
Argumentative:17 A wicked messenger falleth into evil; but a faithful ambassador is health.
Argumentative:19 The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul; and it is an abomination to fools to depart from evil.
Argumentative:20 He that walketh with wise men shall be wise; but the companion of fools shall smart for it.
Argumentative:21 Evil pursueth sinners; but to the righteous good shall be repaid.
Argumentative:22 A good man leaveth an inheritance to his children's children; and the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the righteous.
Argumentative:23 Much food is in the tillage of the poor; but there is that is swept away by want of righteousness.
Argumentative:25 The righteous eateth to the satisfying of his desire; but the belly of the wicked shall want.
Argumentative:Proverbs14 1 Every wise woman buildeth her house; but the foolish plucketh it down with her hands.
Argumentative:2 He that walketh in his uprightness feareth HaShem; but he that is perverse in his ways despiseth Him.
Argumentative:3 In the mouth of the foolish is a rod of pride; but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.
Argumentative:4 Where no oxen are, the crib is clean; but much increase is by the strength of the ox.
Argumentative:5 A faithful witness will not lie; but a false witness breatheth forth lies.
Argumentative:6 A scorner seeketh wisdom, and findeth it not; but knowledge is easy unto him that hath discernment.
Argumentative:7 Go from the presence of a foolish man, for thou wilt not perceive the lips of knowledge.
Argumentative:8 The wisdom of the prudent is to look well to his way; but the folly of fools is deceit.
Argumentative:9 Amends pleadeth for fools; but among the upright there is good will.
Argumentative:10 The heart knoweth its own bitterness; and with its joy no stranger can intermeddle.
Argumentative:11 The house of the wicked shall be overthrown; but the tent of the upright shall flourish.
Argumentative:12 There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.
Argumentative:13 Even in laughter the heart acheth; and the end of mirth is heaviness.
Argumentative:14 The dissembler in heart shall have his fill from his own ways; and a good man shall be satisfied from himself.
Argumentative:15 The thoughtless believeth every word; but the prudent man looketh well to his going.
Argumentative:16 A wise man feareth, and departeth from evil; but the fool behaveth overbearingly, and is confident.
Argumentative:17 He that is soon angry dealeth foolishly; and a man of wicked devices is hated.
Argumentative:18 The thoughtless come into possession of folly; but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.
Argumentative:19 The evil bow before the good, and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.
Argumentative:20 The poor is hated even of his own neighbour; but the rich hath many friends.
Argumentative:21 He that despiseth his neighbour sinneth; but he that is gracious unto the humble, happy is he.
Argumentative:22 Shall they not go astray that devise evil?
Argumentative:But mercy and truth shall be for them that devise good.
Argumentative:23 In all labour there is profit; but the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.
Argumentative:24 The crown of the wise is their riches; but the folly of fools remaineth folly.
Argumentative:25 A true witness delivereth souls; but he that breatheth forth lies is all deceit.
Argumentative:26 In the fear of HaShem a man hath strong confidence; and his children shall have a place of refuge.
Argumentative:27 The fear of HaShem is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.
Argumentative:28 In the multitude of people is the king's glory; but in the want of people is the ruin of the prince.
Argumentative:29 He that is slow to anger is of great understanding; but he that is hasty of spirit exalteth folly.
Argumentative:31 He that oppresseth the poor blasphemeth his Maker; but he that is gracious unto the needy honoureth Him.
Argumentative:32 The wicked is thrust down in his misfortune; but the righteous, even when he is brought to death, hath hope.
Argumentative:33 In the heart of him that hath discernment wisdom resteth; but in the inward part of fools it maketh itself known.
Argumentative:35 The king's favour is toward a servant that dealeth wisely; but his wrath striketh him that dealeth shamefully.
Argumentative:Proverbs15 1 A soft answer turneth away wrath; but a grievous word stirreth up anger.
Argumentative:2 The tongue of the wise useth knowledge aright; but the mouth of fools poureth out foolishness.
Argumentative:3 The eyes of HaShem are in every place, keeping watch upon the evil and the good.
Argumentative:4 A soothing tongue is a tree of life; but perverseness therein is a wound to the spirit.
Argumentative:5 A fool despiseth his father's correction; but he that regardeth reproof is prudent.
Argumentative:6 In the house of the righteous is much treasure; but in the revenues of the wicked is trouble.
Argumentative:7 The lips of the wise disperse knowledge; but the heart of the foolish is not stedfast.
Argumentative:8 The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to HaShem; but the prayer of the upright is His delight.
Argumentative:9 The way of the wicked is an abomination to HaShem; but He loveth him that followeth after righteousness.
Argumentative:10 There is grievous correction for him that forsaketh the way; and he that hateth reproof shall die.
Argumentative:11 The nether-world and Destruction are before HaShem; how much more then the hearts of the children of men!
Argumentative:13 A merry heart maketh a cheerful countenance; but by sorrow of heart the spirit is broken.
Argumentative:14 The heart of him that hath discernment seeketh knowledge; but the mouth of fools feedeth on folly.
Argumentative:15 All the days of the poor are evil; but he that is of a merry heart hath a continual feast.
Argumentative:16 Better is little with the fear of HaShem, than great treasure and turmoil therewith.
Argumentative:17 Better is a dinner of herbs where love is, than a stalled ox and hatred therewith.
Argumentative:18 A wrathful man stirreth up discord; but he that is slow to anger appeaseth strife.
Argumentative:20 A wise son maketh a glad father; but a foolish man despiseth his mother.
Argumentative:21 Folly is joy to him that lacketh understanding; but a man of discernment walketh straightforwards.
Argumentative:22 For want of counsel purposes are frustrated; but in the multitude of counsellors they are established.
Argumentative:24 The path of life goeth upward for the wise, that he may depart from the nether-world beneath.
Argumentative:26 The thoughts of wickedness are an abomination to HaShem; but words of pleasantness are pure.
Argumentative:27 He that is greedy of gain troubleth his own house; but he that hateth gifts shall live.
Argumentative:28 The heart of the righteous studieth to answer; but the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.
Argumentative:29 HaShem is far from the wicked; but He heareth the prayer of the righteous.
Argumentative:30 The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart; and a good report maketh the bones fat.
Argumentative:Proverbs16 1 The preparations of the heart are man's, but the answer of the tongue is from HaShem.
Argumentative:2 All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes; but HaShem weigheth the spirits.
Argumentative:3 Commit thy works unto HaShem, and thy thoughts shall be established.
Argumentative:4 HaShem hath made every things for His own purpose, yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.
Argumentative:5 Every one that is proud in heart is an abomination to HaShem; my hand upon it!
Argumentative:6 By mercy and truth iniquity is expiated; and by the fear of HaShem men depart from evil.
Argumentative:7 When a man's ways please HaShem, He maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.
Argumentative:8 Better is a little with righteousness than great revenues with injustice.
Argumentative:9 A man's heart deviseth his way; but HaShem directeth his steps.
Argumentative:10 A divine sentence is in the lips of the king; his mouth trespasseth not in judgment.
Argumentative:11 A just balance and scales are HaShem'S; all the weights of the bag are His work.
Argumentative:12 It is an abomination to kings to commit wickedness; for the throne is established by righteousness.
Argumentative:13 Righteous lips are the delight of kings; and they love him that speaketh right.
Argumentative:14 The wrath of a king is as messengers of death; but a wise man will pacify it.
Argumentative:15 In the light of the king's countenance is life; and his favour is as a cloud of the latter rain.
Argumentative:16 How much better is it to get wisdom than gold!
Argumentative:yea, to get understanding is rather to be chosen than silver.
Argumentative:17 The highway of the upright is to depart from evil; he that keepeth his way preserveth his soul.
