Argumentative:Nehemiah2 1 And it came to pass in the month Nisan, in the twentieth year of Artaxerxes the king, when wine was before him, that I took up the wine, and gave it unto the king.
Argumentative:2 And the king said unto me: 'Why is thy countenance sad, seeing thou art not sick?
Argumentative:this is nothing else but sorrow of heart.
Argumentative:3 And I said unto the king: 'Let the king live for ever: why should not my countenance be sad, when the city, the place of my fathers' sepulchres, lieth waste, and the gates thereof are consumed with fire?
Argumentative:and when wilt thou return?
Argumentative:9 Then I came to the governors beyond the River, and gave them the king's letters.
Argumentative:Now the king had sent with me captains of the army and horsemen.
Argumentative:14 Then I went on to the fountain gate and to the king's pool; but there was no place for the beast that was under me to pass.
Argumentative:17 Then said I unto them: 'Ye see the evil case that we are in, how Jerusalem lieth waste, and the gates thereof are burned with fire; come and let us build up the wall of Jerusalem, that we be no more a reproach.
Argumentative:' So they strengthened their hands for the good work.
Argumentative:' 20 Then answered I them, and said unto them: 'The G-d of heaven, He will prosper us; therefore we His servants will arise and build; but ye have no portion, nor right, nor memorial, in Jerusalem.
