Argumentative:' And he answered: 'The people are fled from the battle, and many of the people also are fallen and dead; and Saul and Jonathan his son are dead also.
Argumentative:' 11 Then David took hold on his clothes, and rent them; and likewise all the men that were with him.
Argumentative:' 14 And David said unto him: 'How wast thou not afraid to put forth thy hand to destroy HaShem'S anointed?
Argumentative:' 17 And David lamented with this lamentation over Saul and over Jonathan his son, 18 and said--To teach the sons of Judah the bow.
Argumentative:Behold, it is written in the book of Jashar: 19 Thy beauty, O Israel, upon thy high places is slain!
Argumentative:20 Tell it not in Gath, publish it not in the streets of Ashkelon; lest the daughters of the Philistines rejoice, lest the daughters of the uncircumcised triumph.
Argumentative:21 Ye mountains of Gilboa, let there be no dew nor rain upon you, neither fields of choice fruits; for there the shield of the mighty was vilely cast away, the shield of Saul, not anointed with oil.
Argumentative:22 From the blood of the slain, from the fat of the mighty, the bow of Jonathan turned not back, and the sword of Saul returned not empty.
Argumentative:23 Saul and Jonathan, the lovely and the pleasant in their lives, even in their death they were not divided; they were swifter than eagles, they were stronger than lions.
Argumentative:Jonathan upon thy high places is slain!
Argumentative:26 I am distressed for thee, my brother Jonathan; very pleasant hast thou been unto me; wonderful was thy love to me, passing the love of women.
Argumentative:' 2 So David went up thither, and his two wives also, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite.
Argumentative:3 And his men that were with him did David bring up, every man with his household; and they dwelt in the cities of Hebron.
Argumentative:And they told David, saying: 'The men of Jabesh-gilead were they that buried Saul.
Argumentative:' 5 And David sent messengers unto the men of Jabesh-gilead, and said unto them: 'Blessed be ye of HaShem, that ye have shown this kindness unto your lord, even unto Saul, and have buried him.
Argumentative:6 And now HaShem show kindness and truth unto you; and I also will requite you this kindness, because ye have done this thing.
Argumentative:' 8 Now Abner the son of Ner, captain of Saul's host, had taken Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, and brought him over to Mahanaim; 9 and he made him king over Gilead, and over the Ashurites, and over Jezreel, and over Ephraim, and over Benjamin, and over all Israel.
Argumentative:10 Ish-bosheth Saul's son was forty years old when he began to reign over Israel, and he reigned two years.
Argumentative:16 And they caught every one his fellow by the head, and thrust his sword in his fellow's side; so they fell down together; wherefore that place was called Helkath-hazzurim, which is in Gibeon.
Argumentative:' 27 And Joab said: 'As G-d liveth, if thou hadst not spoken, surely then only after the morning the people had gone away, every one from following his brother.
Argumentative:29 And Abner and his men went all that night through the Arabah; and they passed over the Jordan, and went through all Bithron, and came to Mahanaim.
Argumentative:30 And Joab returned from following Abner; and when he had gathered all the people together, there lacked of David's servants nineteen men and Asahel.
Argumentative:31 But the servants of David had smitten of Benjamin, even of Abner's men--three hundred and threescore men died.
Argumentative:7 Now Saul had a concubine, whose name was Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah; and Ish-bosheth said to Abner: 'Wherefore hast thou gone in unto my father's concubine?
Argumentative:' 8 Then was Abner very wroth for the words of Ish-bosheth, and said: 'Am I a dog's head that belongeth to Judah?
Argumentative:9 G-d do so to Abner, and more also, if, as HaShem hath sworn to David, I do not even so to him; 10 to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul, and to set up the throne of David over Israel and over Judah, from Dan even to Beer-sheba.
Argumentative:' 13 And he said: 'Well; I will make a league with thee; but one thing I require of thee, that is, thou shalt not see my face, except thou first bring Michal Saul's daughter, when thou comest to see my face.
Argumentative:' 14 And David sent messengers to Ish-bosheth Saul's son, saying: 'Deliver me my wife Michal, whom I betrothed to me for a hundred foreskins of the Philistines.
Argumentative:' 15 And Ish-bosheth sent, and took her from her husband, even from Paltiel the son of Laish.
Argumentative:17 And Abner had communication with the elders of Israel, saying: 'In times past ye sought for David to be king over you; 18 now then do it; for HaShem hath spoken of David, saying: By the hand of My servant David I will save My people Israel out of the hand of the Philistines, and out of the hand of all their enemies.
Argumentative:' 19 And Abner also spoke in the ears of Benjamin; and Abner went also to speak in the ears of David in Hebron all that seemed good to Israel, and to the whole house of Benjamin.
Argumentative:And David made Abner and the men that were with him a feast.
Argumentative:25 Thou knowest Abner the son of Ner, that he came to deceive thee, and to know thy going out and thy coming in, and to know all that thou doest.
Argumentative:' 30 So Joab and Abishai his brother slew Abner, because he had killed their brother Asahel at Gibeon in the battle.
Argumentative:31 And David said to Joab, and to all the people that were with him: 'Rend your clothes, and gird you with sackcloth, and wail before Abner.
Argumentative:' And king David followed the bier.
Argumentative:' 36 And all the people took notice of it, and it pleased them; whatsoever the king did, pleased all the people.
Argumentative:39 And I am this day weak, and just anointed king; and these men the sons of Zeruiah are too hard for me; HaShem reward the evildoer according to his wickedness.
Argumentative:' 2_Samuel4 1 And when Saul's son heard that Abner was dead in Hebron, his hands became feeble, and all the Israelites were affrighted.
Argumentative:4 Now Jonathan, Saul's son, had a son that was lame of his feet.
Argumentative:5 And the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, went, and came about the heat of the day to the house of Ish-bosheth, as he took his rest at noon.
Argumentative:11 How much more, when wicked men have slain a righteous person in his own house upon his bed, shall I not now require his blood of your hand, and take you away from the earth?
Argumentative:' 12 And David commanded his young men, and they slew them, and cut off their hands and their feet, and hanged them up beside the pool in Hebron.
Argumentative:2 In times past, when Saul was king over us, it was thou that didst lead out and bring in Israel; and HaShem said to thee: Thou shalt feed My people Israel, and thou shalt be prince over Israel.
Argumentative:' 3 So all the elders of Israel came to the king to Hebron; and king David made a covenant with them in Hebron before HaShem; and they anointed David king over Israel.
Argumentative:6 And the king and his men went to Jerusalem against the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, who spoke unto David, saying: 'Except thou take away the blind and the lame, thou shalt not come in hither'; thinking: 'David cannot come in hither.
Argumentative:8 And David said on that day: 'Whosoever smiteth the Jebusites, and getteth up to the gutter, and taketh away the lame and the blind, that are hated of David's soul--.
Argumentative:' Wherefore they say: 'There are the blind and the lame; he cannot come into the house.
Argumentative:' 9 And David dwelt in the stronghold, and called it the city of David.
Argumentative:10 And David waxed greater and greater; for HaShem, the G-d of hosts, was with him.
Argumentative:12 And David perceived that HaShem had established him king over Israel, and that He had exalted his kingdom for His people Israel's sake.
Argumentative:17 And when the Philistines heard that David was anointed king over Israel, all the Philistines went up to seek David; and David heard of it, and went down to the hold.
Argumentative:18 Now the Philistines had come and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.
Argumentative:' And HaShem said unto David: 'Go up; for I will certainly deliver the Philistines into thy hand.
Argumentative:' 20 And David came to Baal-perazim, and David smote them there; and he said: 'HaShem hath broken mine enemies before me, like the breach of waters.
Argumentative:' Therefore the name of that place was called Baal-perazim.
Argumentative:24 And it shall be, when thou hearest the sound of marching in the tops of the mulberry-trees, that then thou shalt bestir thyself; for then is HaShem gone out before thee to smite the host of the Philistines.
Argumentative:5 And David and all the house of Israel played before HaShem with all manner of instruments made of cypress-wood, and with harps, and with psalteries, and with timbrels, and with sistra, and with cymbals.
Argumentative:11 And the ark of HaShem remained in the house of Obed-edom the Gittite three months; and HaShem blessed Obed-edom, and all his house.
Argumentative:12 And it was told king David, saying: 'HaShem hath blessed the house of Obed-edom, and all that pertaineth unto him, because of the ark of G-d.' And David went and brought up the ark of G-d from the house of Obed-edom into the city of David with joy.
Argumentative:17 And they brought in the ark of HaShem, and set it in its place, in the midst of the tent that David had pitched for it; and David offered burnt-offerings and peace-offerings before HaShem.
Argumentative:18 And when David had made an end of offering the burnt-offering and the peace-offerings, he blessed the people in the name of HaShem of hosts.
Argumentative:19 And he dealt among all the people, even among the whole multitude of Israel, both to men and women, to every one a cake of bread, and a cake made in a pan, and a sweet cake.
Argumentative:' 21 And David said unto Michal: 'Before HaShem, who chose me above thy father, and above all his house, to appoint me prince over the people of HaShem, over Israel, before HaShem will I make merry.
Argumentative:22 And I will be yet more vile than thus, and will be base in mine own sight; and with the handmaids whom thou hast spoken of, with them will I get me honour.
Argumentative:2_Samuel7 1 And it came to pass, when the king dwelt in his house, and HaShem had given him rest from all his enemies round about, 2 that the king said unto Nathan the prophet: 'See now, I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of G-d dwelleth within curtains.
Argumentative:9 And I have been with thee whithersoever thou didst go, and have cut off all thine enemies from before thee; and I will make thee a great name, like unto the name of the great ones that are in the earth.
Argumentative:10 And I will appoint a place for My people Israel, and will plant them, that they may dwell in their own place, and be disquieted no more; neither shall the children of wickedness afflict them any more, as at the first, 11 even from the day that I commanded judges to be over My people Israel; and I will cause thee to rest from all thine enemies.
Argumentative:Moreover HaShem telleth thee that HaShem will make thee a house.
Argumentative:12 When thy days are fulfilled, and thou shalt sleep with thy fathers, I will set up thy seed after thee, that shall proceed out of thy body, and I will establish his kingdom.
Argumentative:13 He shall build a house for My name, and I will establish the throne of his kingdom for ever.
Argumentative:' 17 According to all these words, and according to all this vision, so did Nathan speak unto David.
Argumentative:for Thou knowest Thy servant, O Lord G-D. 21 For Thy word's sake, and according to Thine own heart, hast Thou wrought all this greatness, to make Thy servant know it.
Argumentative:22 Therefore Thou art great, O LORD G-d; for there is none like Thee, neither is there any G-d beside Thee, according to all that we have heard with our ears.
Argumentative:23 And who is like Thy people, like Israel, a nation one in the earth, whom G-d went to redeem unto Himself for a people, and to make Him a name, and to do for Thy land great things and tremendous, even for you, in driving out from before Thy people, whom Thou didst redeem to Thee out of Egypt, the nations and their gods?
Argumentative:' 2_Samuel8 1 And after this it came to pass, that David smote the Philistines, and subdued them; and David took Metheg-ammah out of the hand of the Philistines.
Argumentative:And the Moabites became servants to David, and brought presents.
Argumentative:5 And when the Arameans of Damascus came to succour Hadadezer king of Zobah, David smote of the Arameans two and twenty thousand men.
Argumentative:7 And David took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem.
Argumentative:9 And when Toi king of Hamath heard that David had smitten all the host of Hadadezer, 10 then Toi sent Joram his son unto king David, to salute him, and to bless him--because he had fought against Hadadezer and smitten him; for Hadadezer had wars with Toi--and he brought with him vessels of silver, and vessels of gold, and vessels of brass.
Argumentative:13 And David got him a name when he returned from smiting the Arameans in the Valley of Salt, even eighteen thousand men.
Argumentative:15 And David reigned over all Israel; and David executed justice and righteousness unto all his people.
Argumentative:2_Samuel9 1 And David said: 'Is there yet any that is left of the house of Saul, that I may show him kindness for Jonathan's sake?
Argumentative:' And Ziba said unto the king: 'Jonathan hath yet a son, who is lame on his feet.
Argumentative:And David said: 'Mephibosheth!
Argumentative:' And he answered: 'Behold thy servant!
Argumentative:' 7 And David said unto him: 'Fear not; for I will surely show thee kindness for Jonathan thy father's sake, and will restore thee all the land of Saul thy father; and thou shalt eat bread at my table continually.
Argumentative:' 9 Then the king called to Ziba, Saul's servant, and said unto him: 'All that pertained to Saul and to all his house have I given unto thy master's son.
Argumentative:10 And thou shalt till the land for him, thou, and thy sons, and thy servants; and thou shalt bring in the fruits, that thy master's son may have bread to eat; but Mephibosheth thy master's son shall eat bread continually at my table.
Argumentative:' 12 Now Mephibosheth had a young son, whose name was Mica.
Argumentative:2 And David said: 'I will show kindness unto Hanun the son of Nahash, as his father showed kindness unto me.
Argumentative:' So David sent by the hand of his servants to comfort him concerning his father.
Argumentative:And David's servants came into the land of the children of Ammon.
Argumentative:hath not David sent his servants unto thee to search the city, and to spy it out, and to overthrow it?
Argumentative:' 4 So Hanun took David's servants, and shaved off the one half of their beards, and cut off their garments in the middle, even to their buttocks, and sent them away.
Argumentative:5 When they told it unto David, he sent to meet them; for the men were greatly ashamed.
Argumentative:' 6 And when the children of Ammon saw that they were become odious to David, the children of Ammon sent and hired the Arameans of Beth-rehob, and the Arameans of Zobah, twenty thousand footmen, and the king of Maacah with a thousand men, and the men of Tob twelve thousand men.
Argumentative:7 And when David heard of it, he sent Joab, and all the host of the mighty men.
Argumentative:9 Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him before and behind, he chose of all the choice men of Israel, and put them in array against the Arameans; 10 and the rest of the people he committed into the hand of Abishai his brother, and he put them in array against the children of Ammon.
Argumentative:12 Be of good courage, and let us prove strong for our people, and for the cities of our G-d; and HaShem do that which seemeth Him good.
Argumentative:' 13 So Joab and the people that were with him drew nigh unto the battle against the Arameans; and they fled before him.
Argumentative:14 And when the children of Ammon saw that the Arameans were fled, they likewise fled before Abishai, and entered into the city.
Argumentative:15 And when the Arameans saw that they were put to the worse before Israel, they gathered themselves together.
Argumentative:18 And the Arameans fled before Israel; and David slew of the Arameans seven hundred drivers of chariots, and forty thousand horsemen, and smote Shobach the captain of their host, so that he died there.
Argumentative:19 And when all the kings that were servants to Hadadezer saw that they were put to the worse before Israel, they made peace with Israel, and served them.
Argumentative:So the Arameans feared to help the children of Ammon any more.
Argumentative:2 And it came to pass at eventide, that David arose from off his bed, and walked upon the roof of the king's house; and from the roof he saw a woman bathing; and the woman was very beautiful to look upon.
Argumentative:9 But Uriah slept at the door of the king's house with all the servants of his lord, and went not down to his house.
Argumentative:10 And when they had told David, saying: 'Uriah went not down unto his house', David said unto Uriah: 'Art thou not come from a journey?
Argumentative:18 Then Joab sent and told David all the things concerning the war; 19 and he charged the messenger, saying: 'When thou hast made an end of telling all the things concerning the war unto the king, 20 it shall be that, if the king's wrath arise, and he say unto thee: Wherefore went ye so nigh unto the city to fight?
Argumentative:knew ye not that they would shoot from the wall?
Argumentative:why went ye so nigh the wall?
Argumentative:24 And the shooters shot at thy servants from off the wall; and some of the king's servants are dead, and thy servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.
Argumentative:27 And when the mourning was past, David sent and took her home to his house, and she became his wife, and bore him a son.
Argumentative:But the thing that David had done displeased HaShem.
Argumentative:2 The rich man had exceeding many flocks and herds; 3 but the poor man had nothing save one little ewe lamb, which he had bought and reared; and it grew up together with him, and with his children; it did eat of his own morsel, and drank of his own cup, and lay in his bosom, and was unto him as a daughter.
Argumentative:4 And there came a traveller unto the rich man, and he spared to take of his own flock and of his own herd, to dress for the wayfaring man that was come unto him, but took the poor man's lamb, and dressed it for the man that was come to him.
Argumentative:' 5 And David's anger was greatly kindled against the man; and he said to Nathan: 'As HaShem liveth, the man that hath done this deserveth to die; 6 and he shall restore the lamb fourfold, because he did this thing, and because he had no pity.
Argumentative:' 7 And Nathan said to David: 'Thou art the man.
Argumentative:Thus saith HaShem, the G-d of Israel: I anointed thee king over Israel, and I delivered thee out of the hand of Saul; 8 and I gave thee thy master's house, and thy master's wives into thy bosom, and gave thee the house of Israel and of Judah; and if that were too little, then would I add unto thee so much more.
Argumentative:11 Thus saith HaShem: Behold, I will raise up evil against thee out of thine own house, and I will take thy wives before thine eyes, and give them unto thy neighbour, and he shall lie with thy wives in the sight of this sun.
